            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains five letters and one biographical sketch collected by Margaret Underwood Ferguson. The correspondence between Margaret Underwood Ferguson and Clarence W. Alvord discusses submitting her father&#039;s personal papers to the Survey. The biographical sketch of her father, William H. Underwood, describes his life as a district attorney, a state senator, and a delegate to the Constitutional Convention in 1870. He also edited seventeen volumes of the Illinois Supreme Court Reports.</p>
                                 <p>Margaret Underwood Ferguson loaned the correspondence and donated the biographical sketch in 1918.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


